'''''Curse of the Seven Faces''''' is an [[interactive fiction]] video game published by Classic Computing for the [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1984.<ref name="PCW"/> It was re-released later in 1985 by Imperial Software.<ref name="CVG"/> The game was included in a compilation titled ''Assemblage'' in 1986 with three other games. It was published by [[Artic Computing]].<ref name="SU2"/>

==Gameplay==
The objective of the game is to retrieve four objects from an evil wizard: his spell book, staff, hat, and cloak.<ref name="CVG"/> The game had a unique save system at the time: the user has the option to save the game to memory instead to the tape. This was faster than the normal save system.<ref name="PCW"/>

